message: As i said before, Wanggeon was called the Emperor of Goryeo before Mongolian Invasion, and also All Goryeo Monarchs such as Taejo Wang Geon, Wonjong were all Emperors until King Choonryeol "choong" means loyall

I think that it has been proved from Taejo of Goryeo until Wonjong of Goryeo's period was an "Empire". after the Mongolian Invasion although Goryeo have became a Tributary state of Mongolia please reply me as fast as possible.
Changed the status of goryeo from kingdom to "kingdom/empire" because Goryeo was an independent empire before the Mongol invasions
Changed King's title to emperor.
changed king's title to emperor.
Changed King's title to Emperor from Taejo to Weonjong.
changed king's title to emperor.
Changed king's title to emperor.
Jeongjong was also considered as a Emperor along with other following Monarchs.
I have also changed the title from 'King' to Emperor, It has been proved to western historians that Goryeo also has Emperors.

I actually disagree strongly on Goryeo Emperor's being stated as "King"s. I studied in the history and geography at Cambridge University. It has been historically proved that Goryeo Emperors (from Taejo to Wonjong) were considered as Korean Emperors.
